{
    "analysis": "Previous step computed global P95 per metric and found 20 component–KPI pairs with values above their global P95 inside the incident window. The candidates include adservice, cartservice, checkoutservice, and currencyservice; each candidate shows 2 anomalous minutes in-window. We must now use traces to (1) narrow which of these service-level anomalies are on the service call path and (2) identify the most downstream faulty service among them. Trace analysis should use global thresholds computed from full trace series (per trace_name and cmdb_id) and then check for points inside the incident window that exceed those thresholds (for durations/error_rate) or drop below low-percentile for traffic KPIs (row_count). This will help localize the root-cause service.",
